Whereas a stroke, also known as cerebrovascular disease, is an acute neurologic injury that occurs
			 when the blood supply to a part of the brain is interrupted by a clot in
			 the artery or a burst of the artery;

Whereas the permanent health concerns of and treatments for strokes that occur during childhood and
			 young adulthood have considerable impacts on children, families, and
			 society;
